# =============================================================================
# AgentStationHub - repo-wide line ending + encoding policy.
#
# Why this file exists:
#   Windows editors default to CRLF and Windows-1252. Linux containers
#   (Docker, WSL, CI) choke on both: the kernel fails to locate the
#   interpreter referenced by '#!/usr/bin/env bash\r' with a carriage
#   return, and YAML/JSON parsers reject non-UTF-8 bytes. Enforcing the
#   line endings here — checked in LF, checked out LF on all platforms —
#   prevents the "works on my Windows machine, breaks in Docker" cycle.
# =============================================================================

# 1) Default: let git detect text vs binary. Most files.
* text=auto eol=lf

# 2) Shell scripts and anything an in-container shebang touches MUST be LF.
#    A single CR before 'bash' breaks the whole container boot.
*.sh           text eol=lf
entrypoint.sh  text eol=lf

# 3) YAML / JSON / TOML / INI — parsers in Go/Python/Rust tooling are
#    strict about UTF-8 encoding and often dislike CRLF in multi-line
#    strings. Pin them to LF.
*.yml          text eol=lf
*.yaml         text eol=lf
*.json         text eol=lf
*.toml         text eol=lf
*.ini          text eol=lf

# 4) Dockerfile is parsed line-by-line by buildkit; CRLF is tolerated
#    but forces extra 'sed -i' workarounds (see Dockerfile). Normalise.
Dockerfile     text eol=lf
*.dockerfile   text eol=lf
.dockerignore  text eol=lf

# 5) PowerShell + C# are Windows-native, LF is still preferred (cross-
#    platform tooling is happier) and PS + VS read both fine.
*.ps1          text eol=lf
*.psm1         text eol=lf
*.psd1         text eol=lf
*.cs           text eol=lf
*.csproj       text eol=lf
*.razor        text eol=lf
*.cshtml       text eol=lf

# 6) Batch / cmd must keep CRLF — Windows' cmd.exe is the one parser on
#    Earth that actually requires it.
*.bat          text eol=crlf
*.cmd          text eol=crlf

# 7) Markdown is LF everywhere; avoids the "trailing-whitespace renders
#    as line break under CRLF" headache.
*.md           text eol=lf

# 8) Binary files — never touch.
*.png          binary
*.jpg          binary
*.jpeg         binary
*.gif          binary
*.ico          binary
*.pdf          binary
*.zip          binary
*.tar.gz       binary
*.dll          binary
*.exe          binary
*.pdb          binary
*.snk          binary
